'''''Tyrant's Test''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] novel written by [[Michael P. Kube-McDowell]]. It is the third and final installment of the [[The Black Fleet Crisis|''Black Fleet Crisis'']] trilogy, and it was first published in [[December]] [[1996]] by [[Bantam Spectra]].

==Publisher's summary==
''In the wake of a shattered alliance, the New Republic fights a relentless new enemy in an all-new adventure in the bestselling ''Star Wars'' saga&hellip;''

''Faced with an alarming image of Han as a battered hostage of the Yevetha, Chewbacca takes on an urgent mission. Meanwhile, Leia calls upon the Senate to take a stand and eliminate the Yevetha threat&mdash;even at the cost of Han's life. As a former Imperial governor takes his battle to the runaway Qella spaceship, Luke's continuing search for his mother brings him dangerously close to Nil Spaar's deadly forces. And as the Yevetha close in on the forces of the New Republic, Luke takes a desperate gamble with an invisible weapon....''

==Plot summary==
Chewbacca is trying to train his son, [[Lumpawaroo/Legends|Lumpawarrump]], to be a [[Soldier/Legends|warrior]] when the son's test is interrupted by news of Han Solo's capture by the Yevetha. With his son and several other Wookiees, they mount a rescue operation in the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']].

Meanwhile, a petition to recall [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] Leia as president has been issued, causing some issues with the coming war with the Yevetha. Some feel Leia is going to war for selfish reasons.

[[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] and the [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg]] [[Lobot/Legends|Lobot]] unravel truths about the [[Teljkon Vagabond]] as it roams [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], with a former Imperial governor in Lando's [[Luxury yacht/Legends|luxury yacht]] in pursuit.

Luke Skywalker and [[Akanah Norand Goss Pell|Akanah]] wake in [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] to find themselves in an embrace. Their search leads them directly into the coming war with the Yevetha.

